snippet.textDisplay: I only saw yesterday just how expensive mobile data is in the US and Canada. In the UK we can get unlimited 4G for like Â£15 (less than $20), with no caps (well sort of, I am allowed 1000GB and then they check to make sure I am not using it commercially, they won't even cut it off after 1TB, as long as you actually aren't - that said 4G will not allow for much more than that if downloading at full speed for the full 31 days constantly, anyway)... Google Fi, which is just due to launch - is trying to lower data prices over there and is going to be $50 for a similar tariff. That is crazy, you must be paying quite a bit more than that right now...
